There was a day when a rep from a brand told me and my friend @smittyyy24 that if we wanted to increase women shoppers that we needed a “real woman” who wears women’s clothing to accomplish that. It took me a minute to share this story because I’m still in shock by his choice of words.

I’m so thankful that @iamaprilwalker x @beijamvelez made themselves available and showed up made it an epic event. 
When I told April she said” give me the date and I’m there”
The importance of maintaining great relationships with great people is so important.

“The clothes we wear,don’t define who we are” 

Dear brands… be mindful of who you hire as they represent you.

To celebrate Juneteenth the @j.a.y.academy hosted its 2nd annual “Black on the Block” celebration. We were able do gift 200 bikes,helmets,shoes and socks to the kids who attended. 

WHY BIKES???

Childhood obesity is on the rise in the United States and worsened with the pandemic when children had limited access to be physically active.  It's recommended that children are active at least 60 minutes everyday.  However some children in under resourced communities like Milwaukee do not have access to ways to be active.  Encouraging children to ride bikes is one way to provide physical activity for their bodies and help with their mental health.

Sneaker Story #40: The Community Builder.

adidas Forum (since 1983): Forum Low CL “Day One”.

@ShakeJMJ, my next special guest, breathes, thinks, and feels his community in 🇺🇸 Milwaukee, WI. This explains why the kick-off to his “Day One” collaboration with @adidas started with an event that hosted over 100 students who designed their own socks, hats, shirts, and shoes. Inspiring, right? Well, this is just the beginning, 🌍 World. Read my interview with Milwaukee’s Community Builder to get boosted by his positive thinking and deeds. Who knows? Shake’s Sneaker Story might even empower you to become a better person. ✌🏻

Tony23: Why did you choose to showcase your adidas Forum Low CL “Day One” in this episode of the Sneaker Story?
Shake: I always want to be true to who I am. I chose the Forum Low CL because I love that sneaker. I also feel like the people can tell when it is not an authentic collaboration. 
 
Tony23: What is the inspiration behind this collaboration of yours with adidas?
Shake: My inspiration was to send a message to the youth that some words get lost as far as what a “day one” really is. A day one is a person who leads you down on right path and is there for you to support you morally, physically, and things in that nature. I wanted to remind the kids that life is about choices. Therefore, they should choose their day ones wisely. This is the story I wished to tell through the sneakers.

Tony23: What does the brand with the three stripes mean to you in three words?
Shake: Culture, Creativity & Community.
